<h1>Home Page</h1>
<p></p>
	
	<div id="center">This is the home page. Here you will see a list of all the people in the database. It may be initially empty now but as you add people it shall duly populate. This font end application layer is conducive to manipulate data at your own volition. You should see
a person's name, surname, age, gender, income, email, postcode and msisdn. </div>
<p></p>


<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Surname</th>
    <th>Age</th>
    <th>Gender</th>
    <th>Income</th>
    <th>Email</th>
    <th>Postcode</th>
    <th>MSISDN</th>
  </tr>

<% @persons.each do |person| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= person.name %></td>
    <td><%= person.surname %></td>
	<td><%= person.age %></td>
    <td><%= person.gender %></td>
	<td><%= person.income %></td>
    <td><%= person.email %></td>
    <td><%= person.postcode %></td>
    <td><%= person.msisdn %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Show', person %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_person_path(person) %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', person, :confirm => 'Are you sure?', :method => :delete %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
</table>

<p><%= link_to 'Add a new person', new_person_path %>


